The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 The Gail (India) Ltd board has recommended a 40 per cent final dividend on the paid-up share capital in addition to an interim dividend of 40 per cent paid earlier, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The board has recommended payment of total dividend at the rate of 80 per cent for 2004-05, it said. 

 Ness Technologies of Israel has decided to set up a research and development centre for embedded software services in Bangalore. The new centre will carry out a three-year offshore contract for a Swiss company, Bridgeco, providing it with additional product customisation, testing and development.

 Delhi State Industrial Development Corporation (DSIDC) will set up an industrial park in Senegal to enhance mutual cooperation with the African nation. Senegal is keen on active cooperation between the two countries and greater investments from Indian entrepreneurs.

 Accord Software amp; Systems Pvt Ltd has been selected by Isro for its India remote sensing spacecraft programmes. It is the first company to have indigenously developed a GPS-based spacecraft positioning system.

 The Swaraj Engines board will issue two bonus shares for every one held by its shareholders. In addition to this, the board has also recommended a 225 per cent dividend for 2004-05, the Chandigarh-based firm has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Simbhaoli Sugar Mills has filed an offer document with Sebi for a rights issue to raise up to Rs 52.70 crore for funding its capital expenditure. The company has proposed to offer 87.84 lakh shares of Rs 10 each at a premium of Rs 45-50 to its existing shareholders in the ratio of 4:5.

 Mahavir Spinning Mills has declared a 45 per cent dividend for the financial year 2004-05. The company board has also recommended bonus shares in the ratio of 1:2, that is, one share for every two held by the shareholders, the textile manufacturing company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Alps Industries, the owner of the Vista Levolor brand of home furnishes, has launched a range of drapery rods under the Sherwood Collection. The rods are available in single and double brackets.

 ICI Paints has launched Colour Futures 2005 ? a collection of shades based on an annual forecast of international colour trends. The collection is available in 49 unique shades under the Dulux Velvet Touch brand. 

